goals.question: What is the distribution of restaurant types in the University District?
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the variety of cuisines available in the area and can inform decisions about opening a new restaurant.

goals.question: What is the average latitude of restaurants in the University District?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of latitude vs. restaurant count
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the concentration of restaurants in the area and can inform decisions about opening a new restaurant.

goals.question: What is the distribution of latitude values in the University District?

goals.question: What is the relationship between cuisine type and latitude in the University District?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of cuisine type vs. latitude
goals.rationale: This helps to understand if certain cuisines are more concentrated in certain areas of the University District.

goals.question: What is the distribution of the number of restaurants per cuisine type in the University District?

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.countplot(x='key', data=data)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of restaurant types in the University District?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='lat', y='key', data=data, alpha=0.5)
    plt.title('What is the average latitude of restaurants in the University District?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.ylabel('Restaurant Count')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lat', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude values in the University District?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Latitude')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
